           var scrollPos = $(window).scrollTop();
           var textBlockOffset = $('#myTextBlock').offset().top;
           if (scrollPos >= textBlockOffset) {
               $('#myTextBlock').addClass('enlarged');
           } else {
               $('#myTextBlock').removeClass('enlarged');
           }
       });
   });
   ```

3. **CSS**: Define the `.enlarged` class with a `transform: scale()` property and a `transition` on the base element for a smooth animation.
   ```css
   .text-block { transition: transform 0.3s ease; }
   .enlarged { transform: scale(1.2); }
